Class IpInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.wifi.IpInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public final class IpInfo
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Provides IP information of a Wi-Fi connection.

    IP information includes the IP address, gateway address, and DNS server address.

      • getIpAddress

        public int getIpAddress​()
        Obtains the device IP address of a Wi-Fi connection.

        The IP address is an integer. For example, 192.168.1.100 can be converted to the integer (192 << 24) + (168 << 16) + (1 << 8) + (100).

        Returns:
        Returns the device IP address; returns 0 if no device IP address is available.
        Since:
        1

        Returns:

      • getNetmask

        public int getNetmask​()
        Obtains the network mask of a Wi-Fi connection.

        The mask is an integer. For example, 255.255.255.0 can be converted to the integer (255 << 24) + (255 << 16) + (255 << 8) + (0).

        Returns:
        Returns the network mask; returns 0 if no network mask is available.
        Since:
        1

      • getLeaseDuration

        public int getLeaseDuration​()
        Obtains the IP address lease duration of a Wi-Fi connection.

        The lease duration (in seconds) is provided by the DHCP server. If the DHCP server does not provide a lease duration, the default duration is 0xffffffff.

        Returns:
        Returns the IP address lease duration; returns 0xffffffff if the lease duration is not specified.
        Since:
        1
